The tenant of Bakal: The stalls are heating up, he signed a higher rent.
An imposing elderly man walked out the door of the RPG Byty company's customer center from the "coal bar" Zdenek Bakal, the largest private owner of apartments for rent in the Czech Republic.
He was carrying under his arm a file with three new leases for three apartments: his own, that of his daughter and that of his son who is serving a sentence.
The deregulation has increased the rent for these three people.
Instead of paying 3500 the son will have to pay from next year for a 2+1 second category apartment 4100 kroner.
“And there is no hot water and the heating works with solid fuel,” he points to his son’s new contract, the man who has the signature power.
"But I signed anyway," he said, half angry and half resigned.
The citizen association of the BytyOKD.cz apartments, which described the new rental conditions as "immoral and indecent", advises tenants not to sign and wait until December 7, when a notice will be published to explain the method to follow to claim.
But the man reacts to this with a hand gesture.
"One says this, the other says something else" frowning.
The Ostrava region becomes the laboratory of deregulation.
After the New Year, this is what awaits most apartments in the Czech Republic whose rents do not match the market price.
Aktualne.cz has therefore decided to personally visit the "laboratory".
The RPG waiting room in Havirovska street is one of four in the Ostrava region and it is already full on Tuesday at 9 a.m.
Right next to the door stands a security company guard with a device to call customers.
A special button, "rent 2011", is lit on the touch screen.
A single press and a paper with a number comes out of the device.
You don't have time to read your number "157" as your number is already starting to light up on the big screen under the topit of the waiting room.
In a split second, it's your turn.
After a short moment, an old couple arrives to inquire about the rent, but the new rents do not seem to concern the people in the waiting room.
The majority of people have come to solve common problems like everywhere else - requests for repairs, insurance events and so on.
In the Ostrava region, people from more than 44,000 apartments in the RPG portfolio have been receiving mail with new leases in their mailboxes since about mid-November.
RPG Byty offers rent increases of 15 to 38 percent.
The special window for new rents has been open to the public since November 18.
"It's been working for almost a week, so it's still on trial," replies, after a moment of hesitation, the employee behind the counter when the client introduces himself as a journalist.
Deregulation and the former miners’ apartments in Bakal are a very sensitive local subject.
The vice-president of the parliament and native of the Ostrava region Lubomir Zaoralek of the Social Democrats reported this in a fairly sustained way before the elections and this now fills the local newspapers.
“Twenty years after them, I want a new floor.”
"They didn't even change me a fucking board in the toilets," the man said in the introduction.
However, it is mostly, according to employees, retirees who come to be sure they will receive a discount on the new rent price if they sign now as promised RPG in a special offer.
This is a discount of half the amount of the rent that will be received by the other tenants who have signed their new contract before December 15.
But the "deregulation" window on Havirovaska street is really not overwhelmed by questions.
“Of the 360 customers who came yesterday, only 40 to 50 came for the rent,” the employee said at the counter.
And yet RPG offers both on its website and in the showcases individual interviews on rents when necessary.
If the two parties do not agree on the rent, it is an independent court that will make the decision.
“It’s not about threats but just informing about the unique and legitimate way to act legally,” RPG said on its website.
“Nobody will go to court here,” thinks one of the RPG Byty employees, and the man in the street in front of the customer center gives him the reason.
“I have 13,000 crowns of retirement and I have 5,000 crowns left to eat, I don’t have enough to go to court,” he says.
The employee suddenly feels uncomfortable.
"We'll see."
"Mr. Zaoralek in the media asks that no one sign and so people wait," she says.
The regulation of rents ends in the Czech Republic with the beginning of 2011 and increases, according to RPG Byty, are an economic necessity.
"And, moreover, the current rents still do not reach the level necessary for the simple maintenance of the fund for housing," recalls Pavel Klimes, director of the residential portfolio of the company RPG Byty, that it is precisely the negligence of the fund for housing that makes the tenant angry is the main reason for the increase in rent.
However in 5 years between 2005 and 2010 RPG was able with rents to invest in apartments 4 billion, in four years from 2011 to 2014 that should make 5.2 billion.
The large screen hung from the ceiling in front of the upholstered armchairs in the waiting room on Havirosvka Street, however, repeats some information indicated in red.
“The rent increase in 2011 is 15 percent and concerns no less than 31,200 apartments or more than 90 percent of RPG apartments.”
"And it will always be no more than 7.50 CZK per m2 per month," the screen reads.
The 38 percent increase concerns only 400 apartments in the RPG portfolio.
"In these cases, this is an increase of a really very low sum of 19.66 Czech crowns per m2", adds RPG.
Next year the rent will remain the same for 2,600 apartments.
RPG Byty promises that deregulation will not cause a radical but gradual increase over 4 to 8 years.
It adds other commitments: all the money from the rent increase (cf. the graph) is returned to the apartments in the form of heating savings - new windows and heating.
Those who sign the agreement on the rent increase have priority.
The nursery school is also part of the offices have included the architects.
The Avriopoint administrative building in Brno is the new headquarters of the company Arch. Design.
No one could have expected it to also house a mini kindergarten with everything you need - colorful walls, imaginative furniture, toys and finally a miniature playground on the terrace.
Since October of last year, the children of the employees of Arch. design can go there.
The architectural project company Arch. Design. whose workshops have produced a large number of constructions in Brno, has been imagining its mini business nursery school since the first drafts of the Avriopoint building.
She employed about 90 people, mostly from childbearing age, and cared that women architects and project managers could quickly return to work.
At the same time as reduced-time employment contracts, kindergarten is a bonus offered to its employees by the company Arch. Design. as part of its social program.
Builders and architects thus have the opportunity to combine work that takes care of children.
It was the employees of Arch.Design themselves who conceived this kindergarten and with the support of management they were able to obtain an endowment from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.
The Mini Nursery School is financed by the European Social Fund through the Operational Programme of Human Resources and the State Budget of the Czech Republic.
They were able to purchase equipment and appliances and after two years ensure a qualified staff as well as the start-up.
After the use of the funding endowment (two years) the company Arch. Design. has the obligation after 3 years to operate the mini kindergarten on its own funds.
The preparation of the project took a year and it was the company Economy rating that helped to apply for staffing.
The children are cared for by qualified staff, a nurse and a kindergarten teacher take care of the children all day long. children can go to kindergarten without age limitation but they are more than three years old for the most part.
As it is a "mini kindergarten" there can only be 5 children present at the same time, but during the day there are more who replace each other.
The operation of the school is flexible according to the needs of the parents and the children of all employees have the same right to use this school without regard to the hierarchical position.
Although it is an individual care and education, the mini kindergarten program is comparable to that for preschool education.
Children do not only play, but quality education is also ensured - from the beginning to the preparation for school benches, English is taught.
The classroom is equipped not only with imaginative toys and games but also with a computer that children can use.
The presence of small children in society creates a friendly and positive environment.
Parents can at any time control their child and not have the stress of being late to pick up the children at a school away from the parent's workplace.
Parents use their time in the most productive way.
It is not surprising that a natural relationship of loyalty is created between the employee and the employer.
Arch.Design.s is thus registered among the companies that offer a bonus of choice for the recruitment of new employees and that are friendly towards the family and through this program strengthens the marketing of HR.
The bone house still fascinates after 100 years. Take a look at the interiors of Gaudi.
The roof resembles the back of a prehistoric Saurian, the staircase to a dinosaur spine and the balconies to open fish mouths.
This is the Casa Battlo house in Barcelona by the architect Antoni Gaudí.
Due to its organic forms, the house has received from the locals the nickname of Bone House.
Organic shapes, wild colors, unusual use of stones, fragments of tiles and mosaic, facade reminiscent of scales and everywhere present curves, that is all that is epic for the Art Nouveau of Antoni Gaudí.
The front facade of the house unfolds its dream lines, colors and pleasant textures that recall nature and animals.
During a more detailed observation we see the geometry, the rhythm and the order thought with precision.
At night the facade of the house becomes even more dramatic and is lit in such a way that the impression of brightness of colors is reinforced.
The winding and twisting of the shapes also appears in the interiors with the same measure.
The wood copies in waves the window frames, the balustrades, the decorative elements of the doors, the eyelet and the slats.
The Battlo house that stands in the Eixample district in the shopping street Passeig de Gracia at number 43, was born from the construction of an 1877 house by the architect Emilio Sala Cortes.
The reconstruction took two years and the house was completed in 1906.
The investor, Joseph Battlo, a wealthy entrepreneur, first insisted on the demolition of the old construction and the construction of another brand new one but quickly accepted Gaudi's idea of an unusual and cheaper reconstruction.
But the idea of Casa Battlo as a multi-dwelling house was not conceived by Gaudí alone.
The architect Josep Maria Jujol worked with him.
It was precisely on his project that the decorations for an apartment representing the owner of the building and the use of the mosaic for the facade were born.
For the facade also worked other artists and creators.
The joint work for the Casa Battlo plans began with a successful cooperation between Jujol and Gaudi.
Jujol participated in the construction of Gaudí's Casa Mila and Guell Park in which there are other works by Gaudí.
The locals nicknamed the hot house just after it was finished because of its organic shapes "the Bone House".
Others, considering the specific mechanism of opening the windows, called it "the house that leans".
It is said that at the top of the building there is a sword similar to that of Saint George, the patron saint of Catalonia.
Other sculptural elements of the building contain hidden religious motifs.
Gaudi thought for the house a unique system in its time of central heating, with ventilation vents and typical fireplaces.
Their 45-degree tilt seems odd.
During the creation Gaudi did not respect at all the building guidelines of then and did not allow himself to be hindered by them.
At the beginning of the construction he obtained from the city the permit to build, knowing, of course, that the data on the reconstruction plans were so vague that two years later during the finishing the municipal council was horrified and asked for changes.
For example, the members of the city council did not like that the pillars of the construction encroached on the public sidewalk.
There was never any modification, but, on the contrary, only 15 days after the call of the city Josep Battlo requested (and obtained satisfaction) permission to rent the two highest floors.
The owner moved to the lower floors.
In the gallery on the second floor there was a common living room and on the third one bedroom and a private part of the apartment.
The ground floor was rented to a jewellery store.
The entire six-storey house is shared by a staircase through which you access to an independent roof terrace.
All right angles and straight lines were cancelled by the basic elements of the reconstruction and their replacement by curved walls.
Gaudi also worked on the modern concept of connecting spaces.
The common part can be connected completely by opening the doors of the lounges and the high society can communicate comfortably or limit the private space for more intimate interviews.
The house with the reconstruction of Gaudí has also received new facades a non-traditional roof and two more floors.
Gaudí’s play with light is also impressive, with blue and white glass tiles with which the inner courtyard is decorated and with the wells of lights.
The two-color play gives maximum light in all floors of the house.
It was enough simply to bet on the principle that white reflects more than dark, which on the contrary absorbs the sun’s rays.
The Casa Battlo house that was listed in 2005 in the UNESCO World Heritage Fund can be visited by everyone.
On the first floor of the house is the most spacious and beautiful apartment accessible to the public.
The owners decided to take this step in 2002 on the occasion of the 150th anniversary of the birth of the famous designer.
They continued the visits as they found it to be a lucrative venture and they expanded the scope of visits to the common areas and attic including rooftop terraces.
The entrance ticket to the monument is really cheap and costs 16.50 euros; students, retirees, groups and tourist cardholders get 20 percent off.
The sum is still above the price of entry to Gaudí's other buildings in the city.
If you want to feel the real atmosphere of the house with its fantastic turrets, you must quickly find a comrade among the inhabitants of the building and visit the house completely.
How to choose a mattress and bedspread: women have other criteria than men.
No ostentatious frame, but rather the quality of the area reserved for bed, so the mattress and the bedspread give a real basis for a good bed.
They must of course complement each other harmoniously to please a specific user.
During the choice several things are determining,:weight, height, age, health status as well as the sex of the owner.
The type of interior in which we will place the mattress and the backrest is also important.
A typical example?
For example, in the country house where latex mattresses are not continuously slept, they are not suitable because they "warm up" gently.
In addition, they have a higher weight than standard polyurethane mattresses.
It is necessary to return them frequently.
If they also do not have enough ventilation channels in the heart and if they remain, in addition, on a solid board, they retain moisture. Mold can also form there.
Habit is also decisive in the choice.
The one who spends the light of time abroad where very thick mattresses with a softening layer are frequently used, will hardly feel good on a low and hard surface.
“That’s how all the hockey players who come back from the NHL complain that they can’t sleep there.”
“For their tired shoulders, feet and ribs, they needed mattresses with a softening layer of lazy foam.”
"Such mattresses are also recommended for people who suffer from diabetes who have a disorder of the nervous system who therefore misunderstand the 'information' of the joints and skin," explains Sylva Adamczikova who specializes in upholstered furniture.
That is why a few years ago the mattress with lazy foam conquered the hokey players as well as other customers.
"Today everything is going well, for example, Tempur, the Italian Magnifex but also the Czech Tropico have suitable mattresses.
You don't have to be an NHL guy to be able to enjoy a lazy foam.
This "miracle" simply works.
It optimizes its rigidity and shape according to the heat absorbed or adapts to the heat of your body.
Nothing puts pressure on you and you won’t turn around in the night like after a tough match.
You just sleep better.
Lazy foam also works as a protection against sprains.
To choose the mattress according to your size, add the length of the feet, about 21/34 cm.
A man and a woman with a size of 180cm therefore need a bed of 210/220 cm.
The minimum width for each for a double bed should be 90 cm or 180 cm in all.
For single beds, singles for example, it is recommended to take at least 120 /140 cm.
It is convenient in case of a visit.
'However there is a simple rule for the width of the bed: when you are lying on the back you should lay your hands comfortably with the elbows slightly bent.Helena Prokopova, President of the Association of Borreliers-mattresses and decorators who for several years is dedicated to the problem of healthy sleep and the ergonomics of the specialized furniture and teaches it in the schools.
For a two-seater bed everyone needs their own bedspread and mattress, so be careful however during the purchase to choose the height of the mattress well.
Otherwise you will only have to mount the bedspread at different heights and this is not feasible on all bed frames.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, mattresses with springs at least 15 cm, of this count for the layer of shape and ventilation at least three centimeters.
"When touching or sitting on the mattress you should not feel the springs," warns Helena Prokopova.
Each mattress requires a well-determined type of bedspread.
The bedspread, when the mattress and bedspread are united like Siamese sisters, has nothing to do in the bedrooms.
The mattresses looked very bad; it should not be washed, which is commonly done today.
And since during the night one normally sweats from 0.2 to 0.75 l of sweat it is clear that after 5/7 years, the mattress begins to recall a large (and clogged) sieve.
For this reason, the specialists refuse to make a claim over a lifetime of 25 years for a mattress or a lifetime warranty.
But all his own.
And for this a tip of experience from the sellers: for a mattress of 120/140cm, forgo, for the coating of the mattress, hygiene or washing but instead add a protective mattress that you can easily remove and wash.
And even if nowadays it is common to make zipped coatings for the whole, that is to say that after opening one has two parts (for the washing and the size of the washing machine it is very important!) otherwise the manipulation for the large models (and for only one person) becomes when they are removed a fight between a light weight and a heavy weight on a ring.
Do you have a rigid board in your bed instead of a bedspread?
Never, ever!
Maximum for a bed intended for visitors for one night only.
However equip the board (if there are no) with aeration holes and use the spring mattress with a minimum height of 15cm with bag springs (from Germany Taschenfederken) and an aeration layer.
A polyurethane mattress should not be part of such a bed.
For single-position laminate bedspreads with 14/18 lamellae, latex mattresses or so-called sandwiches (perhaps the combination of latex and coconut), are the ideal but it will always be better for you to have a mattress with more lamellae, 28 and above, where the lamellae are lined as well as rigid in the lower part of the kidneys possible
For multi-position mattresses it is not necessary to take a spring mattress because it does not respond to changes in position.
In addition to the adjustment of the rigidity of the strips, it is also possible to install what is called a shoulder cradle.
It is a special connection of the lamellae that allows to press or even to tilt the lamellae so that the shoulder of the sleeper "integrates" well.
For men who have “shoulders as wide as the back,” this is really an important thing.
This thing is already considered by the manufacturers of mattresses that for the "males" have started to use a softening area at the level of the shoulders.
But they also think of women - they again offer them a softer surface at the hips.
For the most difficult customer there are wing or wafer beds with what is called a multiforce suspension.
The pressure spreads to more points and depletes the tension.
But of course, be careful, as soon as you use a bad pillow (large and inflated with air) on good mattresses and bedspread, the "plus" disappears.
The basic rule is a simple pillow: the pillow should support the head and its tips should reach only the shoulders, so that the shoulder muscles can rest.
The recommended size is 50X60 cm that Scandinavians for example prefer.
When lying on the side, the pillow should level (with the cradle of the shoulder of the bed mattress or the area softened in the mattress) the height of the shoulders.
Modern mattresses still have something in common with the first ones based on straw and herbs.
Manufacturers still use natural materials or mixtures.
The trend is also for organic mattresses.
Petroleum-based raw materials, from which polyurethane is made, are replaced by natural oils, such as soybean oil.
Almost all known manufacturers use just soybeans.
“The organic label for mattresses means that the heart is made from natural products,” explains Petr Vasicek of Tropico Plus.
Natural materials are also used for mattress linings; one of the first was aloe vera.
But you can add micro-capsules that develop forest or lavender scents.
There are differences between man and woman.
While birch plant extract so that the mattress lining absorbs heat and cools the body, "cools" the man, the linings "heat" the women.
Red pepper extract accelerates blood circulation and is therefore warmer for the weaker sex.
Current favorites?
Mattresses made from cold foam (it has more pores with a disturbed cellular structure therefore more breathable than standard polyurethane and has more elasticity.
The combination of different stiffnesses of cold foams gives polyzone mattresses that know precisely where the head, lower back and feet are located.
You will pay for a quality mattress from 7000 crowns and more.
Those that are characterized by their parameters for health have less VAT and are taken as instruments for health.
In the Czech Republic, Gumotex reached the first place.
Saving for the mattress and bedspread is not easy.
From time to time two mattresses can be obtained in special actions by manufacturers or producers for the price of one.
For example, the company Magniflex offers Duofreeze mattresses with Memory foam sewn to the coating for 11990 crowns.
Of course, you can take the second one for free.
The era of lazy or viscoelastic foams with an open cellular structure and great thickness was started with Tempur material at a "cosmic" pace.
This started as matter for NASA because astronauts were subjected to enormous load factors at start-up.
Tempur softens in the heat and hardens in the cold.
It therefore adapts perfectly to the warm human body and distributes optimal pressure to it.
It is therefore ideal against bad sleep and for an increase in comfort during sleep.
Viscoelastic foams are used not only for mattresses but also for health products, such as special foot cushions that relieve the legs and venous system.
Czech manufacturers use for example EucathermC or Twinsaver foam or the same type.
Devices to track people are increasingly being demanded by parents who want to monitor their children.
Fear for their child leads more and more people to think about monitoring them through a GPS.
The system, set up at the beginning to search for cars can also be used to trace the movement of people and help for some cases such as that of the little Anicka Janatkova.
The instrument is currently as big as a matchbox but will soon be about the size of a watch.
The case of little Anicka moved a large number of people and they began to look for ways to better protect their children.
Even if the price is to disturb their privacy.
“We are trying to tell everyone that this is not espionage but just another way to reduce the likelihood of another tragedy,” says Petr Pilin of MAcro Weil, one of the suppliers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
"I admit that there may be cases of misuse of such devices, such as putting it in the bag of a person who is not aware of it, but I have not yet encountered such cases."
“The majority of people are customers who actually buy the product for safety reasons,” Pilin adds.
According to him, children should always know for what purposes "the box" is used and how to use it in an emergency.
The child psychologist, Dana Bockova, draws attention to the fact that if the child does not want to carry something of this type on him, he will get rid of it.
“Even the youngest can show great creativity when it comes to intentionally getting rid of something when they don’t want to be under control.”
“Mobile phones, which can be cut like these tracking devices, have already led parents to long expectations,” Bockova said.
According to her, the fact that this type of device can help in case of aggression is highly questionable.
"If it is a prepared abduction, the perpetrator will do everything to ensure that the child does not have an electronic device that can locate him."
“Right now it’s the phone.”
"As soon as the tracking devices are developed, they (the criminals) will also pick them up because the sale will be supported by an advertising campaign."
"In such cases the criminals will always be ahead of the police," says the psychologist.
She admits, however, that such devices can help during an assault not prepared by a paedophile.
According to Robert Cech of the company RC Monitoring, which offers tracking services for both cars and people, having this type of device can help, even if it is destroyed in the event of an assault.
"The device can be set in such a way that it is in regular emission after a specified period."
"In the event that the device is destroyed, the last position of the person concerned remains."
"The more expensive devices also have an inclinometer that immediately signals the position of the person who slipped and ends up in the lying position without moving," says Cech.
According to him, so-called smart mobile phones that are equipped with a navigation system, can offer a comparable service after having formatted it with special software.
The problem with current tracking systems is that it is either a device similar to those worn as a matchbox-sized pendant or to the smallest telephone devices.
We can always lose them.
According to Pilina of the company Macro Weil, this is why tests are currently being conducted to make devices that look like common digital watches.
"This will have the advantage that the potential aggressor will not be able to recognize the tracking device."
"Or he will realize it after a while, which will give the police a little more time," he added.
Whether the tracking device is developed in the form of a bracelet or pendant, it will always use the same technology as for tracking cars.
It is a combination of GPS position acquisition systems (which is commonly used in self-navigation) and a cell phone function that alerts a vehicle's current position.
The army has so many detonating strings that it could go around the Czech Republic with. But it can only last two years.
The army bought for 445 km of ropes used for explosives.
Already last year the Ministry of Defense had purchased 224 km.
The army has reserves for 225 years.
The problem is that the lifespan of the strings is two to four years maximum.
The army bought detonating ropes from the STV Group for 40 million kroner.
The general staff gave as reason for the purchase of a huge amount of detonating ropes at MF DNES that the soldiers use 60 km per year.
According to the reserve calculations made by the army pyrotechnicians, which MF DNES contacted, it appears that even generals, officers with a command, secretaries or household personnel should have an explosives exercise every year.
Alexander Vondra, Minister of Defence and Vlastimil Picek, commander of the army are no exception.
Only to argue the annual consumption of the army of 60 km of detonating ropes.
This distance corresponds to 25,000 explosions.
And even if that were true, the army reserves could sustain it for 10 years.
If, on the contrary, it is true that for the basic training of each of the new professionals it is enough at most 2 m of detonating ropes, as the experts say, it means that the army with its new purchase has secured - with also the consumption of special units and engineering - reserves for the 225 years mentioned.
Yet the soldiers of the Rapid Response Brigade recently complained to Minister Vondra that they have almost no ammunition for their handguns and that shooting sessions are limited due to the need for money.
