This was established for the safety of pyrotechnicians and to be able to more flexibly obtain more modern and reliable types of detonating ropes.
The Ministry of Defence is currently having serious problems with the neutralization of dozens of tons of ammunition from the time of the Warsaw Pact when the Czechoslovak army of two hundred thousand men was preparing to move, heading for the Rhine.
What awaits in a few years this Czech army that MF DNES contacted: neutralize hundreds of kilometers of old detonating ropes that it buys today "cheap".
