At the Land Fund in Plzen, police made arrests during a public competition
In the Land Fund building in Pilsen, anti-corruption police have made arrests in recent days.
The detectives handcuffed the local contractor and real estate trader Lubos. G.
The latter had endeavoured to precisely manipulate a public tender for the settlement of a request for restitution in such a way that the proposed land was obtained by a particular candidate.
He had to pay Lubos G. half a million crowns.
"For the moment I can only confirm that the police are prosecuting a person for insider trading in the context of a public call for tenders and a competition," the head of the prosecutor's office in Plzen, Antonie Zelena, told the Pravo newspaper, knowing that it is forbidden to provide further explanations as the investigation is ongoing.
Police released the 46-year-old entrepreneur after 24 hours.
To find out how he could influence a public competition, one can only speculate on the basis of so little official information.
Speaking to Pravo, Lubomira Cerna Land Fund spokeswoman said that the police had actually made an arrest in Plzen at a separate workplace during the public competition.
"It was a customer and in no case an employee," she said.
The public competition according to Cerna has as its real name "Call to propose rights for the transfer of land according to the Law on the land" and is set up when several candidates manifest themselves as beneficiaries of law.
"These individuals propose, as part of the appeal, a higher value of their redemption rights that must be settled before the value of the land is announced."
"According to the proposed rights, a classification of the buyers is set up and the Land Fund then transfers the land to the person who proposed the highest rights," the Fund's spokesman said.
Lubos G. had, of course, the information concerning the persons who had registered for the appeal and, as he himself was also a beneficiary because he had purchased a large number of rights to restitution, he had proposed to the candidates for the field not to participate in the competition.
And he probably paid for it by withdrawing.
Which would explain why he had so much money in his possession at the time of his arrest.
