“The good news is that the dogs are fine,” Whitmore said.
“They are in good shape.”
"They were returned to their rightful owners."
Whitmore declined to say exactly where the dogs had been found, in what neighborhood and what the circumstances of their discovery were.
"An investigation is underway."
“We don’t want to say it,” Whitmore said.
"We follow orders."
The owners of the dogs, Kristina Rickard and David Peek, could not be reached to provide a comment Thursday.
They were reunited Wednesday afternoon with their two Akitas at a county animal shelter in Downey.
Sheriff's deputies found the van and the two dogs separately in Compton.
