This is necessary in order to embarrass the Iranian regime, sensitive to its image.
“Do it all the more because the Iranians are asking you not to do it.”
For, having passed the attempts of discussions through discreet channels, "silence will not solve anything", the Iranians are "masters in dilatory maneuvers".
Richier added that the arrest of foreigners is “a familiar Iranian tactic: taking hostages for political blackmail.”
